<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-03-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-03-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="495" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">812.113/9226</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Mexican Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bonillas</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi></p>
                            <p>The Mexican Government wishes to know if it is possible for the
                                United States Government to sell to the former, rifles which were
                                used by the American Army before the war.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <dateline rendition="#left">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-18">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 18, 1919</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>